The Mpumalanga Community Safety Department says it&#8217;s not clear what caused the crash. JOHANNESBURG The festive season traffic rush has claimed more lives, this time in Mpumalanga, where three people have been killed and one left injured after a taxi collided head on with a another vehicle.Officials say the injured person, who was an occupant in the taxi, is in a critical condition at a local hospital after the accident last night.The Mpumalanga Community Safety Department says it s not clear what caused the crash and an investigation is underway.Department spokesperson Moeti Mmusi says, The police are still investigating the cause of the accident, it s not yet clear what might have led to the collision yesterday. Two of those who were fatally injured were in the minibus while the one person who died was an occupant in another vehicle. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)